sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects usage of the 'chattr' utility to remove immutable file attribute.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Execution Of Script Located In Potentially Suspicious Directory
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects executions of scripts located in potentially suspicious locations such as "/tmp" via a shell such as "bash", "sh", etc.

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=/bin/sh sh -c "for f in /etc/crontab /var/spool/cron/root /var/spool/cron/crontabs/root; do [ -f \"$f\" ] && sed -i '/\\/tmp\\/\\.\\(kswapd\\|khelper\\|watchdog\\|rcu_sched\\|ksmd\\|ksoftirqd\\|kworker\\|migration\\)/d' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null; done; pkill -9 -f '/tmp/\\.\\(kswapd\\|khelper\\|watchdog\\|rcu_sched\\|ksmd\\|ksoftirqd\\|kworker\\|migration\\)' 2>/dev/null || true"; Image=/bin/sh; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects chmod targeting files in abnormal directory paths.
